questionRound.0.question.9.answer: From the last person's likely decision to get my own decision
start with last players best optin and go backwards

I would first look at all the possibilities that I have  then in retrospect  I will look at what the options are possible for the other colors. I would select the one that will give others the maximum  as well that gives me the maximum in comparison to other three options.
I started at the payoff for the last player because that person had the last say and worked my way backwards by predicting what others were going to pick as their payoff.

I would look first what others would chose depending on my choice and then see what would lead to a better outcome for me. However  if I was the last person to make a decision  I would just look at the first person and then decide accordingly.
I would see what token the last player in each game would select  by comparing the probabilities  and using this one  | token you can tell what everyone else will select by following the tables.

I had to think about what the other players would choose to maximize their own profits.  I would start from the right hand side was  where the player would use the first player's known choice to benefit them most.  Then I used the answer they chose to see what the second to last person would pick to maximize their profits  and so forth.  If I was first  I would pretend to choose one option  go through the process  and determine my earnings.  Then I would do the same with my other choice  and compare the results to find the more profitable option.  Of course  this did rely on trusting the other people playing with me to be smart and not just pick randomly.
